2164.subject: MLML
2164.descrlong:
MLML 142:Phys Oceanograph-  An introduction to the nature and causes of various oceanic motions, including currents, waves, tides, and mixing; and the physical properties of seawater. Limited use of calculus. Offered through Moss Landing Marine Laboratories (MLML); contact SEP program office for MLML registration procedures. (Offered fall semester.)

(Prereq: Include Junior and Senior and Post Bac and Graduate)
